1.description: Translate expert clinical knowledge and research relevant to midwifery into best practice models.

2.description: Develop, implement and evaluate projects to improve women’s health care.

3.description: Interpret and apply research related to the national and international distribution and determinants of health and disease of women and newborns.

4.description: Evaluate women’s health policy issues within a variety of jurisdictions (local to federal), and demonstrate the ability to develop remedies to promote health improvement for women and newborns.

5.description: Use effective communication and leadership skills to enhance team function and promote positive change in the health care of women and newborns.

6.description: Analyze theories relevant to the discipline of midwifery, and apply these theories to inform and evaluate the health care of women and newborns.

7.description: Evaluate and use information systems and other technologies to improve the quality and safety of health care for women and newborns.

8.description: Analyze and compare health care delivery and finance models to improve health outcomes for women and newborns.

9.description: Develop expertise and share knowledge in a selected area of midwifery practice or scholarship.
